title: The Unstoppable Rise Of LG TVs (There's No Catching Up)
description: 💡 Turn any idea into a production-ready app or website by describing it to AI. Dream it, and Lindy builds it from coding to QA. Try Lindy today using my link 👉🏻 https://go.lindy.ai/logically-answered   In the early 2010s, OLED was a joke. Too fragile, too expensive, and impossible to scale. Everyone dropped it except LG. Fast forward to today, and LG owns over half the global OLED market. They even make panels for Samsung and Sony. So what did LG see that everyone else missed? Back in the 2000s, the TV world was all Plasma and LCD. Plasma had the best picture but came with heat, power, and burn-in issues. LCDs were cheap, efficient, and “good enough.” While everyone chased scale, LG doubled down on quality. They bought Kodak’s OLED patents, poured billions into R&D, and invented WRGB OLED to cut costs. For years, it looked like financial suicide. But when Netflix, gaming, and home theaters exploded, OLED became the gold standard. By 2016, LG had perfected manufacturing, and by 2017, the C7 OLED changed everything. Competitors mocked OLED, then bought LG panels anyway. Now, LG Display supplies Samsung, Sony, and nearly every major brand. The bet no one believed in became the tech no one could live without. title: Best TV of 2025 (Shootout): LG G5 vs Samsung S95F vs Sony BRAVIA 8 II vs Panasonic Z95B
description: Our 2025 TV shootout between the LG G5 & Panasonic Z95B 4-stack WOLED TVs + Samsung S95F & Sony BRAVIA 8 II QD-OLEDs.  All competing TVs were 55 inches in screen size, and were calibrated in SDR and HDR modes to the common standards used within the film and broadcast industry, perceptually matched to a Sony BVM-HX3110 dual-layer LCD mastering monitor capable of reaching a peak brightness of 4000 nits.  All the TVs were masked, so the 6 video professional & sole enthusiast judges didn't know which TV was which when scoring different picture attributes.  00:00 Intro 00:21 Near-black 00:57 Colours 02:12 HDR 03:38 Motion 04:31 Uniformity 05:02 Video processing 05:52 Bright room 06:14 Out of The Box 06:48 Best Home Cinema TV 07:33 Best Living Room TV 11:23 Best TV of 2025 12:37 Shootout format  The judges were (in alphabetical order by surname):  1. James Meredith, Technical Director & Co-Founder at Netvio 5. Julian Nelson, Head of Post Production & Co-Founder at Residence Pictures 6. Luis Pinhao, Imaging Engineer at Cinelab Ltd 7. title: Besser als OLED? Micro-RGB-TVs sind die Zukunft!
description: Samsung stellt mit Micro RGB eine völlig neue Display-Technologie vor, die OLED ernsthaft Konkurrenz machen könnte. In diesem Video erklären wir euch, was hinter Micro RGB steckt, wie sich die Technik von Mini-LED und Micro-LED unterscheidet und warum sie als nächste große TV-Innovation gilt.  Wir zeigen, wie Micro RGB durch winzige farbige LEDs statt weißem Licht für bessere Helligkeit, mehr Kontrast und eine präzisere Farbdarstellung sorgt. Außerdem erfahrt ihr, warum die Technologie eine Brücke zwischen LCD und Micro-LED sein könnte und ob sie OLED wirklich ablösen kann.  Die im Video gezeigten Produkte bei MediaMarkt kaufen: Samsung S95F 77 Zoll: https://mmr.ms/RbhuJq  Zum Magazin: LCD vs. OLED: Was ist besser?: https://mmr.ms/H-K$oW  Kapitel: 0:00 Intro 2:08 Was ist Micro RGB? 6:47 Kein echtes Micro-LED? 7:58 Endlich die Wachablösung für OLED?  🔔 Wenn euch unsere Videos gefallen, dann abonnieren und Glocke drücken nicht vergessen! ☞ https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCip1RVSGWtkukxd0Am1NiRQ?sub_confirmation=1  💬 Wir freuen uns über euer Feedback oder Videowünsche in den Kommentaren.  🕔🕛 Neue Videos erscheinen jeden Donnerstag, 17 Uhr und jeden Sonntag, 12 Uhr. title: Samsung S90F QD-OLED: ANÁLISE COMPLETA + Comparativo C5 e S90D
description: 🔥Link de compra da S95F (em promoção): https://curt.link/iEtTO 🔥Link de compra da S90F: https://curt.link/dGbMx Cupom: VEMPROCLUBE  📱Entre no nosso Canal de Ofertas: https://linkmc.click/ofertas 📝Entre no nosso grupo de conteúdo: https://linkmc.click/newsmc  Análise completa da nova Samsung S90F, TV OLED da marca coreana que acaba de chegar ao Brasil. O modelo traz a tecnologia QD-OLED, que combina o painel OLED da Samsung (sem subpixel branco) com pontos quânticos, permitindo alcançar picos de brilho de até 1500 nits em janelas de 10% no modo HDR. Isso representa uma melhora considerável em relação à geração anterior, com aproximadamente 30% de ganho em brilho.  A S90F mantém os principais atributos da tecnologia OLED, como o preto super profundo e o contraste infinito, agora acompanhados de um volume de cor muito bacana, resultado da combinação das tecnologias exclusivas da Samsung. Além da imagem, a TV também traz melhorias no som. Conta com áudio de 40W em um sistema 2.1 canais, oferecendo uma experiência sonora mais encorpada. No sistema operacional, a S90F já vem equipada com o novo Tizen 2025, que adota a interface One UI — mesma interface presente nos smartphones da Samsung — e que agora está sendo integrada também aos eletrodomésticos conectados da marca, como parte da estratégia de criar um ecossistema unificado.  Em termos de inteligência artificial, a TV traz mais recursos embarcados graças a um chip mais poderoso. Entre as novidades estão o AI Vision, agora com suporte a karaokê, e o recém anunciado Copilot, que ainda não foi testado, mas representa uma nova funcionalidade que deve chegar em breve. É importante destacar que a S90F não é o modelo topo de linha da Samsung em 2025. Esse título continua com a S95F, que promete alcançar picos de brilho superiores a 2.000 nits.  00:00 - Destaques 02:10 - Design 05:47 - Sistema 10:00 - Qualidade de imagem 17:10 - Esportes 19:12 -
